	Novel auction    
	 London, Oct. 15 (PTI): A first edition of George Orwells classic 1984, found in a charity shop by a bargain hunter, is all set to go under the hammer in Australia.       
	The rare edition is estimated to fetch several thousand dollars and will be auctioned this weekend. The proceeds of the auction will be donated to Lifeline, an Australian crisis support hotline, Contactmusic reports.       
	The hardback was printed in 1949. It was picked out by Paul Hol out of a heap of literary donations at a charity store in Wollongong.    
	Jolie role    
	 Los Angeles (PTI): Oscar-winner James Cameron is in talks to direct Angelina Jolie in a new 3D film based on the life of Egyptian queen Cleopatra. Based on Stacy Schiffs book Cleopatra: A Life, the 3D movie is being produced by Scott Rudin and the Avatar director is a favourite to helm the project. Jolie, who is currently busy shooting her directorial debut, a Bosnian love story, has already confirmed her interest in the role, Deadline.com reports.     
	Gaga tears    
	 London (PTI): Pop star Lady Gaga grew teary eyed as she paid a special tribute to her late grandfather, who passed away last month, during a concert. Gaga dedicated her ballad Speechless in honour of her grandfather, reports Contactmusic.     
	Betty play    
	 London (PTI): Ugly Betty star America Ferrera is set to make her West End debut with a play that will see her play a plain jane all over again. The 25-year-old is in talks to make her London theatre debut in a play that explores inner beauty.                                                                                                                                                      
